    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Genesis",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 15,
        "summary": "Abram desires offspring\u2014The Lord promises him seed in number as the stars\u2014Abram believes the promise\u2014His seed will be strangers in Egypt\u2014Then, after four generations, they will inherit Canaan.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "After these things the word of the Lord came unto Abram in a vision, saying, Fear not, Abram: I am thy shield, and thy exceeding great reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vision.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 26:24; 1\u00a0Ne. 22:17. TG\u00a0Courage; Fearful.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Protection, Divine.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Abram said, Lord God, what wilt thou give me, seeing I go childless, and the steward of my house is this Eliezer of Damascus?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 24:2.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Abram said, Behold, to me thou hast given no seed: and, lo, one born in my house is mine heir.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0a son of my house. Gen. 14:14.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And, behold, the word of the Lord came unto him, saying, This shall not be thine heir; but he that shall come forth out of thine own bowels shall be thine heir.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he brought him forth abroad, and said, Look now toward heaven, and tell the stars, if thou be able to number them: and he said unto him, So shall thy seed be.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0count.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 10:22; Neh. 9:23; D&C 132:30.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Chr. 27:23.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Seed of Abraham.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 158
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he believed in the Lord; and he counted it to him for righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Gen. 15:9\u201312 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said unto him, I am the Lord that brought thee out of Ur of the Chaldees, to give thee this land to inherit it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 32:18.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said, Lord God, whereby shall I know that I shall inherit it?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Judg. 6:17 (17\u201318); 2\u00a0Kgs. 20:8 (8\u20139); Luke 1:18 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said unto him, Take me an heifer of three years old, and a she goat of three years old, and a ram of three years old, and a turtledove, and a young pigeon.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he took unto him all these, and divided them in the midst, and laid each piece one against another: but the birds divided he not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 34:18 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when the fowls came down upon the carcases, Abram drove them away.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell upon Abram; and, lo, an horror of great darkness fell upon him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:15 (15\u201317).",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said unto Abram, Know of a surety that thy seed shall be a stranger in a land that is not theirs, and shall serve them; and they shall afflict them four hundred years;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Bondage of, in Egypt; Stranger.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 1:11 (10\u201311); 1\u00a0Ne. 17:25 (23\u201325).",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 149
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And also that nation, whom they shall serve, will I judge: and afterward shall they come out with great substance.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 2:24; 1\u00a0Ne. 5:15; 19:10; Mosiah 12:34; Alma 36:28; D&C 136:22.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 12:36.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thou shalt go to thy fathers in peace; thou shalt be buried in a good old age.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Old Age.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But in the fourth generation they shall come hither again: for the iniquity of the Amorites is not yet full.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Note in Ex. 6:16\u201320 that four generations of Levi's descendants are named; they include (1)\u00a0Levi, (2)\u00a0Kohath, (3)\u00a0Amram, (4)\u00a0Moses. TG\u00a0Israel, Bondage of, in Egypt.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 3:17.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 17:35 (32\u201335); Alma 37:31; Hel. 13:14; Ether 2:9 (8\u201310); D&C 61:31; 101:11.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass, that, when the sun went down, and it was dark, behold a smoking furnace, and a burning lamp that passed between those pieces.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 34:18 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In the same day the Lord made a covenant with Abram, saying, Unto thy seed have I given this land, from the river of Egypt unto the great river, the river Euphrates:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abrahamic Covenant.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 13:15 (14\u201317); Josh. 1:2 (2\u20134). TG\u00a0Israel, Land of; Promised Lands.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the Wadi El Arish in northern Sinai. Ex. 23:31; 1\u00a0Kgs. 4:21.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 122
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 11:24 (22\u201325).",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Kenites, and the Kenizzites, and the Kadmonites,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Hittites, and the Perizzites, and the Rephaims,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Amorites, and the Canaanites, and the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}